        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[The Knowledge and The Manual for Civilization]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[<article><h1>The Knowledge and The Manual for Civilization</h1><p>One of the early inspirations for creating the Manual for Civilization was an email I received from Lewis Dartnell in London asking me for information on a book he was writing inspired by James Lovelock’s “Book for all Seasons”.  The idea was a kind of reboot manual for humanity, and it coincided well with some other conversations we had been having at Long Now about making a collection of books that could do something similar.</p><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/the-grid-img/p/3d7df2dfed93bb87efe500ce84390ae299a455eb.jpg"></article>]]></description>
            <link>http://blog.longnow.org/02014/04/19/the-knowledge/</link>
